Package com.intellij.xdebugger.frame

Interface XCompositeNode

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Obsolescent
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ChildrenBuilder
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EvaluatingExpressionRootNode, WatchesRootNode, WatchNodeImpl, XStackFrameNode, XValueContainerNode, XValueGroupNodeImpl, XValueNodeImpl

    public interface XCompositeNode
extends Obsolescent
    Represents a node with children in a debugger tree. This interface isn't supposed to be implemented by a plugin.
    See Also:
    XValueContainer

      • tooManyChildren

        void tooManyChildren(int remaining)
        Add an ellipsis node ("...") indicating that the node has too many children. If user double-click on that node XValueContainer.computeChildren(XCompositeNode) method will be called again to add next children.
        Parameters:
        remaining - number of remaining children or -1 if unknown
        See Also:
        MAX_CHILDREN_TO_SHOW
